content:
To apply the action to the object's page layout, go to Setup in Salesforce and enter the name of the object (e.g. Opportunities) in the Quick Find box. Select Page Layouts and edit the page layout assigned to the profile for the users who need access to the action.

Click the Opportunity Layout link next to a profile, then click Quick Actions in the palette. Drag the Update Opportunity custom action to the existing actions in the Salesforce Classic Publisher section. If predefined actions are overridden, also drag the action to the Mobile & Lightning Actions section and save.

This adds the action to the page layout for the object, making it visible on record detail pages for users assigned that layout.
title: Customizing Salesforce Page Layouts
